By Onyebuchi Ezigbo The federal government has imposed a temporary ban on international flights at the three of the countries international airports. The affected airports are Kano, Port Harcourt and Enugu which is currently undergoing repairs. It said that flights into the country can only be allowed through the Muritala Mohammed International Airport, Lagos and Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport in Abuja. Addressing a press conference on Friday in Abuja shortly after the end of the Inter-ministerial Presidential Committee on Containment of Covid-19, the Minister of Health, Dr. Osagie Ehanire, said the 36 state governments and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) have been asked to set up isolation centres to complement the existing ones. He said that currently, there are about 350 intensive care units across the country designated to cater for coronavirus emergency. While giving an update on the spread of coronavirus in the country, Ehanire said that there are currently 12 confirmed cases, while the earlier two cases — the Italian index case and his main contact — have been treated and discharged. Details later…